         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/9/16 ¶ Copy ¶ Dear Miss King, ¶  ¶ I feel still very poorly so this letter is again by dictation. ¶  The Boronia kindly sent by you from the Hawkesbury River ¶  is the true B. floribunda so your sp...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">96.09.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Georgina King</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Inward correspondence 1854-1900, G. King, Museum of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/9/16</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Copy</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Original letter not found. MS is a copy made by Georgina King.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Miss King,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I feel still very poorly so this letter is again by dictation.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to G. King, 16 September 1896.</p>
               </note> The Boronia kindly sent by you from the Hawkesbury River<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>NSW.</p>
               </note> is the true B. floribunda so your specimens are very valuable and are fixing the locality for certain; you will easily recognise the species in contrast to B. pinnata. I send sketches of the flowers of both<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The sketches, together with M’s letters to King, were shown at the meeting of the Linnean Society of NSW on 28 October 1896; see <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Proceedings of the Linnean Society of NSW</seg>, vol. 21, 1896, pp. 584-5.</p>
               </note> so you will easily understand to discriminate these plants and find out more localities for it, it seems restricted to your region.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have it already in the second census,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B89.13.12, p. 18.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> but willl bring it before the next meeting of the Linnean Society of N.S.W.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>M's note, B97.05.01, was read at the meeting held on 30 September 1896.</p>
               </note> Could you kindly learn from Mr Fletcher its Secretary at Elizabeth Bay when the next meeting will be held. It would be best to bring at once this plant forward instead of waiting to obtain also ripe fruit for which I must look to your kindness hereafter.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>from your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by King, before the signature: '(Signed by the Baron)'.</p>
               </note>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
